6	//! Lazy, composable GPU operations and combinator types.
7	//!
8	//! The [`DeviceOperation`] trait is the core abstraction. Each operation
9	//! describes GPU work without binding to a stream. Combinators (`and_then`,
10	//! `zip`, `apply`, `with_context`) compose operations into dataflow graphs
11	//! that remain stream-agnostic until scheduling time.
12	//!
13	//! # Scheduling model
14	//!
15	//! | Method       | What it does                                                      |
16	//! |--------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------|
17	//! | [`schedule`] | Pairs the operation with a stream, returns a [`DeviceFuture`].    |
18	//! | [`sync`]     | Shorthand: schedule + execute + synchronize on the default device.|
19	//! | [`sync_on`]  | Execute and synchronize on a specific stream.                     |
20	//! | [`async_on`] | Execute on a specific stream **without** synchronizing.           |
